      "contentFieldValue": {
        "data": "<p>Liferay Digital Experience Platform 7.0 is only supported under the following certified configurations: </p>\n<h2><a id=\"application-server\" href=\"#application-server\">Application Server</a></h2>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">JBoss EAP 6.4</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">JBoss EAP 7.0</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">JBoss EAP 7.1</span></li>\n<li>\n<span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">JBoss EAP 7.4</span><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\"></span>\n</li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">tcServer 3.1</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">tcServer 3.2</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Tomcat 8.0</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Tomcat 8.5</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Tomcat 9.0</span></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li>\n<span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Weblogic 12c Release 1</span><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\"></span>\n</li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Weblogic 12c Release 2</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Websphere 8.5.5 Fix Pack 11+</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Websphere 9.0</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Wildfly 10.0</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Wildfly 11.0</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Wildfly 23.0</span></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>For more information on configurations and limitations with Application Servers that are compatible with Liferay DXP, please refer to the <a href=\"https://help.liferay.com/hc/articles/360017895772-Introduction-to-Liferay-DXP-Deployment\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"undefined\">Liferay User Guide</a>.</p>\n<h2><a id=\"database\" href=\"#database\">Database</a></h2>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Amazon Aurora</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">DB2 9.7</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">DB2 10.1</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">DB2 10.5</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Maria DB 10.0</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Maria DB 10.2</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">MySQL 5.6</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">MYSQL 5.7</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Oracle 11g Release 2</span></li>\n<li>\n<font size=\"2\">Oracle 12c Release 1</font><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\"></span>\n</li>\n<li><font size=\"2\">Oracle 12c Release 2</font></li>\n<li><font size=\"2\">Oracle 19c</font></li>\n<li><font size=\"2\">PostgreSQL 9.3</font></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">PostgreSQL 9.4</span></li>\n<li>\n<span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">PostgreSQL 9.6</span><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\"></span>\n</li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">PostgreSQL 10</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">SQL Server 2008</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">SQL Server 2008 R2</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">SQL Server 2012</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">SQL Server 2014</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">SQL Server 2016</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">SQL Server 2017</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">SQL Server 2019</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Sybase ASE 15.7</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Sybase ASE 16</span></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>For more information on configurations and limitations with Databases compatible with Liferay DXP, please refer to the <a href=\"https://help.liferay.com/hc/articles/360017895772-Introduction-to-Liferay-DXP-Deployment\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"undefined\">Liferay User Guide</a>.</p>\n<h2><a id=\"operating-system\" href=\"#operating-system\">Operating System</a></h2>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Alpine Linux 3.8</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Amazon Linux 2</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Amazon Linux 2023</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">CentOS 6</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">CentOS 7</span></li>\n<li><font size=\"2\">Debian 7</font></li>\n<li><font size=\"2\">Debian 8</font></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Debian 9</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">IBM AIX 7.1</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Oracle Linux 6</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Oracle Linux 7</span></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Oracle Solaris 10</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Oracle Solaris 11</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">RedHat Enterprise Linux 6</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">RedHat Enterprise Linux 7</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">SUSE Enterprise Linux 11</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">SUSE Enterprise Linux 12</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Ubuntu LTS 14.04</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Ubuntu LTS 16.04</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Ubuntu LTS 22.04</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Windows Server 2012 R2</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Windows Server 2016</span></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n<h2><a id=\"desktop-browser\" href=\"#desktop-browser\">Desktop Browser</a></h2>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Chrome (Latest)</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Edge (Latest)</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Firefox ESR (Latest)</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Firefox (Latest)</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Internet Explorer 9 (Limited)</span></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Internet Explorer 10 (Limited)</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Internet Explorer 11</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Safari 8</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Safari 9</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Safari 10</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Safari 11</span></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>For more information on configurations and limitations with Desktop Browsers that are compatible with Liferay DXP, please refer to the <a href=\"/w/installation#Browsers\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"undefined\">Support Policy</a>.</p>\n<h2><a id=\"mobile-browser\" href=\"#mobile-browser\">Mobile Browser</a></h2>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Chrome (Latest)</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Safari (Latest)</span></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<p> </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Liferay will support access to information (e.g. reading content and navigation through pages), navigation menus, and basic responsiveness of modules for the latest versions of mobile browsers only. For more information on Liferay’s mobile support policy, please refer to the <a href=\"/w/mobile-device-support-policy\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"undefined\">Help Center</a>.</p>\n<h2><a id=\"jdk\" href=\"#jdk\">JDK</a></h2>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">IBM J9 JDK 8</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Oracle JDK 8</span></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: small;\">All Java Technical Compatibility Kit (TCK) compliant builds of Java 8</span></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>JDK Certification is for runtime only. JDK 8 is required to build or compile Liferay DXP Projects.</p>\n<h2><a id=\"cloud-services\" href=\"#cloud-services\">Cloud Services</a></h2>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2)</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Amazon Relational Database Service (RDS)</span></li>\n<li>\n<span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Amazon S3</span><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\"></span>\n</li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Azure Files</span></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Azure SQL Databases</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Azure Virtual Machines</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Google Cloud Compute</span></li>\n<li><font size=\"2\">Google Cloud SQL</font></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Amazon EC2 and RDS are only supported with environments on the Liferay DXP 7.0 Compatibility Matrix.</p>\n<h2><a id=\"search-engines\" href=\"#search-engines\">Search Engines</a></h2>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li>\n<span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\">Elasticsearch 6</span><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\"></span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\n<ul>\n<li>Solr 5</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Refer to the <a href=\"/w/search-engine-compatibility-matrix\" target=\"_self\">Search Engine Compatibility Matrix</a> for the detailed compatibility including the compatible connector versions and required patch levels.</p>\n<h2><a id=\"notes\" href=\"#notes\">Notes</a></h2>\n<p>Liferay DXP does not restrict the use of VM/Container strategy as long as the Application Server, Database, JDK, and Operating System are certified for use as indicated on the Compatibility Matrix above. Subscribers will be responsible for configuring the VM/Container appropriately.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-small\">Updated 04/06/2023</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-medium\"><a href=\"https://www.liferay.com/documents/10182/246659966/Liferay+DXP+7.0+Compatibility+Matrix.pdf/98fbf692-9ae8-2812-def3-76da2d881301?t=1609783179453\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"undefined\">Download PDF</a></span></p>"
